#: ../../aggregate-install.rst:479
msgid ""
"First, sign up for Amazon Web Services EC2 at "
"`<http://aws.amazon.com/ec2/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../aggregate-install.rst:483
msgid "You will need to confirm a working phone number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../aggregate-install.rst:484
msgid ""
"If you want to use a U.S. number but are presently overseas, you can use "
"a Google Voice number routed to Google Chat."
msgstr ""

#: ../../aggregate-install.rst:486
msgid ""
"Go to the AWS/EC2 management console and note your region (shown in the "
"upper-left)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../aggregate-install.rst:487
msgid ""
"Launch a new instance with the :guilabel:`Launch Instance` button "
"prominently displayed on the EC2 console home screen. Accept the default "
"behavior and use the quick-launch wizard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../aggregate-install.rst:488
msgid ""
"For the launch configuration, choose the :guilabel:`Amazon Linux AMI: "
"EBS-Backed (64-bit)` option. This is one of the instance types that you "
"can run on a micro-instance as part of their `free tier "
"<http://aws.amazon.com/free/>`_. Leave everything else at the defaults, "
"including the instance type. The instance type will default to *t2.micro*"
